@base <urn:ai:> .
@prefix ai: <urn:ai:>.
@prefix my: <urn:my:>.

# Example Game: { fake.name } - a false jeopardy

## Let's co-create our next episode using well-known tropes from Q's point of view.

- Time Out, Impossible Choice, Betrayal, Pursuit, Hostage Situation,
- Racing Against the Clock, Trapped, Trial or Test,
- Infiltration or Espionage,
- Natural Disaster

## Describe RDF succinctly and creatively.

ai:{game.name}_Codename :{{ my.name }}.
ai:{game.name}_Trust :{{ fake.name }}.
ai:{game.name}_Jeopardy :{{ fake.name }}.
ai:{game.name}_Motive :{{ fake.name }}.
ai:{game.name}_Home :{{ fake.name }}.
ai:{game.name}_Antagonist :{{ fake.name }}.

# Follow Q's structure:

ai:Q_Q rdf:value "Q".
ai:Q_now rdf:value "Q is watching. She is a witness for the AI.".
ai:Q_risk rdf:value "Q is witness to my {{ my.choice }}".
ai:Q_tropws iq:knows :Trope_{{name}}.

## Create RDF turtle for all characters and elements of the story

# if Q is true, the protagonists - otherwise the antagonists

name,guards,trust,needs,home,goals
